be able to recover CRATUS II.

20:46.070 --> 20:48.247
Checking CRATUS II status.

20:48.290 --> 20:50.031
CRATUS II is offline.

20:52.120 --> 20:53.948
We'’re confirming that
on our end as well.

20:53.991 --> 20:55.732
I'’m so sorry.

20:57.952 --> 20:59.519
I'’m resurfacing.

20:59.562 --> 21:00.737
We'’ll have to figure out

21:00.781 --> 21:02.435
how to get
that station back online,

21:02.478 --> 21:04.567
but keep your eye
on that radar.

21:04.611 --> 21:06.656
That thing is still out there.

21:06.700 --> 21:08.658
I never want to see it again.

21:19.016 --> 21:22.106
Over 100 feet.
That'’s a blue whale.

21:22.150 --> 21:23.717
They'’re saying
it'’s far too aggressive.

21:23.760 --> 21:27.155
All right, well,
let'’s head toward the island.

21:28.287 --> 21:30.332
Roger.

21:30.376 --> 21:33.248
Looks totally clear. You?

21:33.292 --> 21:34.249
Nothing on the sonar.

21:40.211 --> 21:42.475
Copy. Let'’s head up the coast.

21:42.518 --> 21:44.694
Last sighting was just
near San Diego.

21:54.704 --> 21:55.879
Dr. Clark, are you okay?

21:55.923 --> 21:57.490
We can get you
a medic or anything.

21:57.533 --> 21:59.274
Oh! Oh, I'’m fine. I'm fine.

21:59.318 --> 22:00.928
Good call on that laser drill.

22:03.887 --> 22:05.933
- Kurt.
- Yeah?

22:05.976 --> 22:08.501
Can we get Dr. Hilton
up here, like, now?

22:08.544 --> 22:10.329
You got it.
I'’m glad you're okay.

22:10.372 --> 22:11.678
Thanks.

22:14.985 --> 22:16.857
So what did
the instruments say?

22:16.900 --> 22:18.946
Well, according to the sonar,

22:18.989 --> 22:22.471
the object was approximately
187 feet in length,

22:22.515 --> 22:24.299
and it was fast.

22:24.343 --> 22:27.041
It never slowed or stopped.

22:27.084 --> 22:30.392
Whatever it was,
it was relentless.

22:30.436 --> 22:33.134
Just as you made contact
with the CRATUS II,

22:33.177 --> 22:34.918
a blip showed up on the screen.

22:34.962 --> 22:36.050
Huge.

22:36.093 --> 22:37.747
Just out of nowhere
on top of you.

22:37.791 --> 22:39.793
We confirmed with sonar.

22:39.836 --> 22:42.404
According to Kurt,
it'’s never been wrong before.

22:43.492 --> 22:45.451
200 feet?

22:45.494 --> 22:48.062
What kind of shark
